Jakadan Amurka ya zargi kasar Sin da yin ta'addanci da kuma yada labaran da suka shafi kasar
Jakadan kasar Sin na Amurka ya zargi Beijing da yada labaran da ke yadawa a cikin jaridun Amurka, mako guda bayan wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani sanarwa a cikin jaridar Amurka mai shafuka hudu da ke nuna amfanin da ke tsakanin kasuwancin Amurka da China.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi magana ne a kan wata sanarwa da ya fito a cikin jaridar China Daily Des Moines Register a ranar Laraba da ta gabata, a cikin jaridar mafi yawan sayarwa a Iowa, yayin da ya zargi kasar Sin da kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka na ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba.
Daidai da zargin da Trump ya yi da cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka, wasu jami'an Amurka da suka shaida wa Reuters sun ce wannan sabon mataki ne a matakin da Washington ke dauka na kara tsananta wa kasar Sin, da nufin matsa lamba a kan kasar.
Ko da yake ba abin mamaki ba ne cewa gwamnatocin ƙasashen waje suna tallata kasuwanci da ƙasashensu ta hanyar tallace-tallace, amma ana ci gaba da yin yaƙi da cinikayya tsakanin Beijing da Washington, inda suke ɗora ƙarin haraji a kan kayayyakin da suke shigo da su.
Masana a Amurka da China sun ce a farkon yakin cinikayya, China ta yi amfani da takunkumin da aka yi a matsayin martani don yin niyya ga masu fitar da kayayyaki daga jihohin da Trump da jam'iyyar Republican suka fi so, kamar Iowa.
Terry Branstad, jakadan kasar Sin na Amurka da tsohon gwamnan Iowa, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kuma kasuwanni lahani, saboda jihar Iowa tana fitar da kayayyakin gona masu yawa zuwa China.
Branstad ya rubuta a cikin wata sanarwa a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register a ranar Lahadi cewa, "Sin ta ci gaba da ɓata ƙasarmu ta wajen wallafa labaran da ke nuna cewa muna da 'yancin yin amfani da jaridarmu".
'Gwamnatin kasar Sin tana amfani da al'adun Amirka na 'yancin yin magana da kuma yada labarai ta wajen yin amfani da tallace-tallace da ake yi a cikin littattafan da ake biyan kuɗi a cikin Des Moines Register,' in ji Branstad.
 Amma idan ka je wani kantin sayar da jarida a birnin Beijing, ba za ka samu labarai masu sautin ra'ayi ba.
Branstad ya ce wata babbar jarida a kasar Sin ta ƙi buga labarin, amma ba ta ambata sunan jaridar ba.
